    "A study conducted by Lastra-Díaz et al. [32] and Hussain et al.",
    "[44] provides a detailed categorization of semantic similarity measures.",
    "Semantic Collaborative Filtering RecommendationIn the domain of recommendation systems, collaborative filtering is the most successful technique [1][2][3][4]51].",
    "It is based on the assumption that finding people with similar interests and recommending items that they like in an effective way to provide interesting content.",
    "Collaborative filtering works with user-item historical data, where each user rates items based on their preferences."
